<div class="c230_61">
<div id="v230.61.1"><span class="H5329 s">To the chief Musician</span><span class="H5058 s"> upon Neginah</span><span class="H1732 s">, <i>A Psalm</i> of David</span><span class="H8085 s">. Hear</span><span class="H7440 s"> my cry</span><span class="H430 s">, O God</span><span class="H7181 s">; attend</span><span class="H8605 s"> unto my prayer</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.61.2"><span class="H7097 s">From the end</span><span class="H776 s"> of the earth</span><span class="H7121 s"> will I cry</span><span class="H3820 s"> unto thee, when my heart</span><span class="H5848 s"> is overwhelmed</span><span class="H5148 s">: lead</span><span class="H6697 s"> me to the rock</span><span class="H7311 s"> <i>that</i> is higher</span> than I.</div>
<div id="v230.61.3"><span class="H4268 s">For thou hast been a shelter</span><span class="H5797 s"> for me, <i>and</i> a strong</span><span class="H4026 s"> tower</span><span class="H6440 s"> from</span><span class="H341 s"> the enemy</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.61.4"><span class="H1481 s">I will abide</span><span class="H168 s"> in thy tabernacle</span><span class="H5769 s"> for ever</span><span class="H2620 s">: I will trust</span><span class="H5643 s"> in the covert</span><span class="H3671 s"> of thy wings</span><span class="H5542 s">. Selah</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (trust: or, make my refuge)</span></div>
<div id="v230.61.5"><span class="H430 s">For thou, O God</span><span class="H8085 s">, hast heard</span><span class="H5088 s"> my vows</span><span class="H5414 s">: thou hast given</span><span class="H3425 s"> <i>me</i> the heritage</span><span class="H3373 s"> of those that fear</span><span class="H8034 s"> thy name</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.61.6"><span class="H3254 s">Thou wilt prolong</span><span class="H4428 s"> the king's</span><span class="H3117 s"> life</span><span class="H3117 s"> †</span><span class="H8141 s">: <i>and</i> his years</span><span class="H1755 s"> as many</span><span class="H1755 s"> generations</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Thou…: Heb. Thou shalt add days to the days of the king) (as…: Heb. as generation and generation)</span></div>
<div id="v230.61.7"><span class="H3427 s">He shall abide</span><span class="H6440 s"> before</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H5769 s"> for ever</span><span class="H4487 s">: O prepare</span><span class="H2617 s"> mercy</span><span class="H571 s"> and truth</span><span class="H5341 s">, <i>which</i> may preserve</span> him.</div>
<div id="v230.61.8"><span class="H2167 s">So will I sing</span><span class="H8034 s"> praise unto thy name</span><span class="H5703 s"> for ever</span><span class="H3117 s">, that I may daily</span><span class="H3117 s"> †</span><span class="H7999 s"> perform</span><span class="H5088 s"> my vows</span>.</div></div>
